Definition
Tripleton is a design pattern where:
Only three objects of a class are allowed to be created in the entire application.
It is an extension of the Singleton and Doubleton patterns.
Singleton → 1 object
Doubleton → 2 objects
Tripleton → 3 objects

How Tripleton Works
Constructor is made private
Create 3 static objects
Provide static method to return those objects
Prevent external object creation

